## 4. Database Schema

### Users
- id, email, password, role (patient/doctor/nurse/admin)
- firstName, lastName, phone, avatar
- createdAt, updatedAt

### Patients
- id, userId, dateOfBirth, gender
- chronicConditions (JSON array)
- emergencyContact, bloodType
- assignedDoctorId

### Medical Records
- id, patientId, doctorId
- type (consultation/vital-signs/lab-result/prescription)
- data (JSON), notes
- createdAt

### Appointments
- id, patientId, doctorId
- scheduledAt, duration, status
- type (video/in-person/phone)
- notes, meetingUrl

### Messages
- id, senderId, receiverId
- content, readAt
- createdAt

### Vital Signs
- id, patientId
- type (blood-pressure/heart-rate/blood-glucose/weight/temperature)
- value, unit, recordedAt

---

## 5. Core Features

### Authentication
- Login/Register with email/password
- JWT token-based auth
- Role-based access control

### Patient Management
- List patients (doctor view)
- Patient profile with medical history

### Vital Signs Monitoring
- Dashboard with latest measurements
- Charts for trends

### Appointments
- Schedule consultations
- Calendar view

### Messaging
- Secure doctor-patient chat

### Dashboard
- Statistics overview
- Recent appointments
- Quick actions

